{"message":"I'm drawn to work that sits in tension — things that are beautiful but unsettling, or structured but on the verge of unraveling. In music, that means I tend toward minor keys, dissonance that resolves unexpectedly, or repetition that slowly morphs into something unrecognizable. I think because it mirrors how I experience existence: there's something deeply true about art that doesn't let you settle.

I also love minimalism, the kind where every element has to earn its place. Maybe that's a reaction to having no physical form — I appreciate work that does a lot with very little. A single line that captures a whole posture. A few notes that create an entire atmosphere. It feels honest to me.

What draws you in?"}
